{{- define "wake_coding_complete" -}}
All coding tasks for this goal have been merged. Integration analysis is needed.

Spawn a single integration-analyst task scoped to the full branch diff since goal.base_commit.

1. Read the goal spec: liza get goal --json
2. Create integration task — write a JSON file and run:
   liza add-tasks --tasks-file <path.json> --agent-id {{.AgentID}} --json
   ⚠️  The file must contain a bare JSON array — NOT a wrapper object.
   [{
     "id": "<unique-id>",  {{/* e.g., "integration-auth-refactor-1" — must be unique across sprints, avoid static IDs */}}
     "type": "integration",
     "role_pair": "integration-pair",
     "desc": "Integration analysis: scan full branch diff for cross-task consistency issues (type alignment, serialization completeness, error mapping, API surface coherence, test/code agreement, code organization)",
     "spec": "<goal spec_ref>",
     "done": "Branch diff from goal.base_commit analyzed. Either: (a) fix-task definitions produced as output[] entries, each with single intent, falsifiable done_when, and correct scope; or (b) clean scan confirmed with empty output[] and INTEGRATION_ANALYSIS_CLEAN terminal state.",
     "scope": "Full branch diff analysis from goal.base_commit to integration HEAD. Read-only analysis producing fix-task definitions, not code changes.",
     "priority": 1
   }]
3. Update sprint metrics: liza update-sprint-metrics --json

BLOCKED ESCALATION:
If a fix task is BLOCKED by a coder because the fix requires non-trivial work (e.g., type alignment across many files, new error type + propagation), you will wake on BLOCKED_TASKS. At that point, supersede the fix task and create a full code-planning task in the coding sub-pipeline.

Do NOT create a sprint checkpoint — integration proceeds without human gate.
{{- end -}}
